\intbl \ql \b Background\b0 \line The Boston City Campus and Business College is registered with the Department of Higher Education and Training as a higher education provider and is accredited to offer higher education programmes by the HEQC.\line \line The Diploma in Event Management programme was tabled at the Accreditation Committee meeting of 22 and 23  February 2012 and was not accredited for the following reasons\'3A \line \line 1.The design is flawed. There is no coherent structure for the programme. There are no building blocks for knowledge progression. Level 5 credits are not available\'2C therefore students have to jump from a level 4 knowledge area to level 6\'2C without any building blocks.\line 2. It is not clear how the experiential learning will be supervised and the institution has not accepted responsibility for the placement of students.\line 3. The institution does not have a clear understanding of the needs of the distance mode of delivery. Materials development is not explicitly catered for in its policies.\line 4. The staff members are not all relevantly qualified and experienced\line 5. Given that the registrar and the programme coordinator are the same person\'2C it is not clear that there is sufficient academic expertise to provide academic leadership and curriculum development.\line 6. Resource provision in terms of library resources and computer access is insufficient. The student support for the distance education mode is inadequate.\line 7. There is no description of the number and types of assessments\'2C whether formative or summative\'2C and there is also no evidence of how the overall outcomes will be assessed.\line \line The institution submitted the representation. \cell \pard 

\intbl \row \pard 
\line \par\pard\trowd\trqc \trpaddl113\trpaddt113\trpaddb113\trpaddr113\trpaddfl3\trpaddft3\trpaddfb3\trpaddfr3\trgaph100\trrh100\trleft36
